Yo Felix, I'm the guy who gave his mousepad a bath. It looks great afterwards, the bathtub really works. A few tips though! Use dish soap, and don't use a lot. Use warm water, but a bit less warm than you would wash your hands with. It's recommended to use a microfibre cloth or a sponge and wipe over it with light pressure so you don't damage the coating. Let it air dry. Too much heat will cause the fabric to separate from the rubber side, so do not use a drier. I hung mine over a door, but any sort of hang drying will work, like a clothesline. I'll post an update on the subreddit if it helps.
